cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the automatic classification of diabetic retinopathy using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of pre-trained convolutional neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of non-linear classifiers also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of deep features, which is a common technique in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of annotated datasets, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
